DESERT HEARTS

01:52.735 --> 01:54.479
Excuse me.

01:54.702 --> 01:58.397
Passengers of the super speed
service to Sacramento and Oakland.

01:59.896 --> 02:01.693
can now be on board.

02:06.295 --> 02:08.092
-Can I help you, miss?
-Please.

02:08.999 --> 02:11.796
-I'll bring this for you.
-Thank you.

02:18.992 --> 02:20.788
-Professor Bell!

02:22.696 --> 02:24.492
- You can call me Vivian.
- Welcome to Reno.

02:25.400 --> 02:27.196
-I am down the street.

02:28.104 --> 02:30.900
- Hi Francie.
- Hello, Burnett.

02:30.909 --> 02:32.706
- I have space in my car.
- No, not such luck.

02:36.308 --> 02:39.003
Well, you are looking forward
to some desert living?

02:39.012 --> 02:41.809
I'am looking forward to get
these shoes of.

02:42.716 --> 02:44.513
It's terrible when
your legs hurts.

02:45.420 --> 02:47.217
It's a kindest thing
I've heard in three days.

02:48.124 --> 02:50.819
- How long have you been married?
- 12 years.

02:52.727 --> 02:54.523
No,no. We handle that.

02:55.456 --> 02:57.355
Quint, that's a lucky one. 

02:58.363 --> 03:00.262
I could have used that last night.

03:10.271 --> 03:12.169
See you in six weeks, madam.

03:12.178 --> 03:14.076
Soon as we are out of here you
can tell me all about youself.

03:18.085 --> 03:24.984
I was the special dancer
in casino over there, 100 years ago.

03:27.992 --> 03:29.891
Do you have children??

03:30.900 --> 03:32.798
We were a couple of
professionals.

03:35.807 --> 03:39.705
My husband was a prominent lawyer,
here in town.

03:42.714 --> 03:44.613
- He died of a heart attack at 41.
- Sorry.

03:47.622 --> 03:49.520
How long have you been alone?

03:49.529 --> 03:52.427
I'm not alone, I have my boy.

03:55.436 --> 03:57.334
My girlworks there
in the Golden Ring.

03:59.343 --> 04:02.242
Has the unbridled
Glen force!

04:06.251 --> 04:08.149
I have always lived
in the city.

04:09.158 --> 04:11.056
Do not know what to do
with all this space.

04:12.065 --> 04:14.963
I think of it as a God's backyard.

04:15.972 --> 04:18.870
Just sit back and let
it clean out the impurities.

04:18.880 --> 04:22.778
-And the heat?
-Lot of ice tea and not deep thinking.

04:24.787 --> 04:26.685
I agree

04:28.694 --> 04:30.593
Oh, Jesus!

04:40.601 --> 04:42.500
-What are you doing at this hour?
- I have things to do.

04:44.509 --> 04:47.407
-Professor Bell, Cay Rivers.
-How do you do.

04:51.416 --> 04:54.314
-Shall I call you the professor?
-No, Vivian Bell.

04:56.323 --> 04:58.222
Put that damned car forward!

05:02.231 --> 05:04.129
Jesus!

05:05.138 --> 05:07.036
You'll never guess who that was.

05:08.045 --> 05:10.943
- Do you mind if I smoke?
- Of course not.

05:11.952 --> 05:13.851
Never would have guessed
you smoked.

05:15.860 --> 05:17.758
May I be honest, Frances?

05:18.767 --> 05:20.665
That is an endangered art.
Forward.

05:23.674 --> 05:26.572
My things are a little bit shaky 
for me at the moment.

05:29.581 --> 05:32.480
-Thank you for open up ...
-I can not be a part of group right now.

05:37.489 --> 05:38.387
Leave it to me.

05:39.396 --> 05:41.294
Thank you.

06:24.303 --> 06:27.202
Walter, we are here!

06:32.210 --> 06:35.109
Walter, shake hands
with professor Vivian.

06:36.118 --> 06:38.016
-Hello.
-Hello.

06:38.025 --> 06:41.923
-You are younger than I thought.
-I'll take that as a compliment.

06:42.932 --> 06:44.831
Bring bags, Walter.

06:48.839 --> 06:50.738
You gona love it here.

06:59.747 --> 07:01.645
Well, here it is.

07:02.654 --> 07:04.552
Nice, isn't it?.

07:06.561 --> 07:08.460
Lovely.

07:08.469 --> 07:10.367
-He will take you to your room.
-Thank you.

07:25.376 --> 07:27.274
-The bathroom is over there.
-Thank you.

07:28.283 --> 07:30.181
What do you teach?

07:30.190 --> 07:32.089
Literature at the University
Columbia.

07:33.098 --> 07:35.996
116th Street, Broadway,
New York, New York.

07:42.005 --> 07:44.903
I know you want me to hang around and 
tell you history of the ranch.

07:46.912 --> 07:48.810
How did you guess, Walter?

08:49.819 --> 08:51.718
Why I did not stay in a hotel?

09:13.727 --> 09:17.625
I felt burned and start to yearn

09:17.634 --> 09:19.532
Hold you tight

09:24.541 --> 09:26.440
- Guess what baby girl.
- What?

09:27.448 --> 09:29.347
I am engaged.

09:29.356 --> 09:31.254
-Hello
-Hello, love.

09:31.263 --> 09:33.161
- Isn't it beautiful?
- Careful not to stay blind.

09:35.170 --> 09:36.069
and...

09:38.077 --> 09:40.976
I'm pregnant.

09:41.985 --> 09:44.883
Joe and I are settling down.
Darrel and you should follow.

09:45.892 --> 09:48.790
-We would go on vacation together.
-I feel nothing for Darrel.

09:49.799 --> 09:51.698
I never get tired 
to defend your reputations.

09:52.707 --> 09:54.605
I got used people 
talking behind my back.

09:56.614 --> 09:58.512
but if you did not accept
who I am 

10:00.521 --> 10:02.419
that would really be tought.

10:04.428 --> 10:06.327
Hey, you're the best.

10:06.336 --> 10:09.234
And all the best people 
know it.

10:46.243 --> 10:48.141
Thank you

10:52.150 --> 10:54.048
Good luck. Thank you.

10:55.057 --> 10:57.956
- Would you like to play that, sir?
- Sherman.

10:58.965 --> 11:00.863
Sherman, would you like to play?

11:00.872 --> 11:02.770
I prefer to play with you,
my love.

11:05.779 --> 11:07.678
Apologize to the lady, buddy.

11:09.686 --> 11:11.585
-Apologize, man.
-Sorry.

11:14.594 --> 11:16.492
It makes two of us.

11:16.401 --> 11:18.399
-Thank you.
-You are right?

11:18.408 --> 11:19.307
Yes.

11:39.315 --> 11:42.214
- A cup of tea?
- Frances!

11:44.223 --> 11:46.121
-Do you have any burbon?
-Sure.

11:48.130 --> 11:50.028
In fact, I'll joing you.

11:51.037 --> 11:53.936
Will not do any harm.

11:54.945 --> 11:56.843
It's the weather.

11:58.852 --> 12:00.750
I was reading a lot.

12:01.759 --> 12:03.657
You sound like Cay.

12:04.666 --> 12:07.565
She locks herself in that college
and works until she drops.

12:08.574 --> 12:10.472
-What does she work?
-She is a sculptor.

12:17.481 --> 12:19.379
Oh, don't look at that stuff

12:20.388 --> 12:24.287
It is sentimental junk.
I have no taste.

12:27.295 --> 12:29.194
That is Glen, Cay's father.

12:31.203 --> 12:33.101
I had Walter with him.

12:35.110 --> 12:37.008
I'm not the mother of Cay.

12:38.017 --> 12:39.916
I'm her ...

12:39.924 --> 12:41.823
I do not know what I am.

12:44.832 --> 12:46.730
Not anything really.

12:47.739 --> 12:49.637
Only one pair of hands 
and a familiar face.

12:52.646 --> 12:54.545
Thank you

12:56.554 --> 12:58.452
God, look at him.

12:59.461 --> 13:01.359
As handsome as day is long.

13:01.368 --> 13:03.266
And married.

13:05.275 --> 13:08.174
I lived with him 10 years.

13:11.183 --> 13:15.081
Maybe I didn't get my wedding
bouquet in my collection.

13:15.090 --> 13:17.000
But I got what I wanted.

13:18.997 --> 13:20.895
I had a love of my own.

13:22.904 --> 13:24.803
That song is beautiful.

13:26.812 --> 13:28.710
You had more than 
most people dare hope for.

13:33.719 --> 13:35.617
Do not pay attention.

13:35.626 --> 13:37.525
I'm just babbling.

13:42.533 --> 13:44.432
I am a silly woman.

13:47.441 --> 13:49.339
I don't think you are, Frances.

14:13.348 --> 14:14.246
Hi.

14:18.255 --> 14:20.154
You and me should make
a raisins pie.

14:21.162 --> 14:24.061
-I'm too depressed.
-In this air?.

14:24.070 --> 14:26.968
Will you well be fine when you 
leave that creep.

14:27.007 --> 14:29.000
Larry is not a creep 

14:29.884 --> 14:31.783
Any man who leaves a woman 
for a model is a creep in my book.

14:33.792 --> 14:35.690
I do not know which is worse.

14:35.699 --> 14:37.597
A cheeter or a hobby man.

14:39.606 --> 14:41.504
At least you can share 
a hobby, Lucille.

14:42.513 --> 14:44.412
We would all like to
have a different past.

14:46.421 --> 14:48.319
Good morning!

14:48.328 --> 14:50.226
Good morning.

14:52.235 --> 14:54.133
-I come down to stretch my legs.
-It's was about time.

14:55.142 --> 14:57.041
What did you do in that room 
for last five days?

14:58.050 --> 15:00.948
Whatever it is, it is too deep 
for us to understand.

15:03.957 --> 15:05.855
Come, sit down.
Join the girl talk.

15:06.864 --> 15:08.763
We talked about sex 
vs. marriage.

15:09.771 --> 15:12.670
I'm not an expert on these issues 
so I apologize.

15:13.679 --> 15:15.577
I heard that your culture types
go out like a bench sheet.

15:15.586 --> 15:18.484
- Lucille!
- Is that true?

15:20.493 --> 15:23.392
A bench sheet is a woman 
weeping for the dead.

15:25.400 --> 15:27.299
Perhaps you wanted 
to say "monkeys".

15:27.308 --> 15:28.206
Hey!

15:30.215 --> 15:33.113
Well, I'll start with my pie. 

15:35.122 --> 15:37.021
Lucille, would you drop Cays' mail?

15:38.030 --> 15:40.928
I'll take it.

15:40.937 --> 15:42.835
Just going for a walk, anyway.

15:43.844 --> 15:45.742
Just slip it under her door.

15:51.751 --> 15:53.650
You do not have to knock!

16:03.659 --> 16:05.557
- Morning!
- Morning!

16:25.566 --> 16:27.464
I was just passing by.

16:30.473 --> 16:32.371
Thanks.

16:37.380 --> 16:39.279
Do you want to come in?

16:40.659 --> 16:43.557
-I'd love to but you're busy.
-Come in anyway.

16:49.566 --> 16:51.464
To see if I can see it all
in one glance.

16:52.566 --> 16:54.464
Look around.

17:07.473 --> 17:09.371
I can't do it if you are watching me.

17:15.380 --> 17:17.279
- Hello!
- Hey....!

17:18.288 --> 17:19.185
Hello

17:19.194 --> 17:22.093
-Where is Cay?
-I am here. Go back to sleep.

17:25.102 --> 17:27.001
Sorry. I was not alone.

17:26.102 --> 17:29.001
Fine. Socialization
was not what I had in mind, anyway.

17:40.009 --> 17:42.908
You get all that traffic  
without any equipment?

17:44.009 --> 17:46.908
I can not understand.

18:12.917 --> 18:15.815
-Where are you going?
-To an appointment with the lawyer. 

18:16.824 --> 18:18.722
No sense in taking two cars?

18:18.731 --> 18:20.630
-I do not want to intrude.
-Will you bring her back?

18:20.646 --> 18:23.545
Oh, don't worry about that.
Give space, Gwen.

18:23.554 --> 18:27.452
You have a car for today
and I save the trip.

18:32.461 --> 18:34.359
Cay, drive like a lady.

18:35.368 --> 18:37.266
Someone used it as an ashtray.
Come in front. 

18:44.275 --> 18:46.174
Long time without seeing you, Mrs. Parker.

18:48.183 --> 18:50.081
Doesn't bother me.

18:55.090 --> 18:57.988
-This is my friend, Gwen.
-We met.

18:58.997 --> 19:00.895
Yes, nice to see you again.

19:18.904 --> 19:20.803
-Are you serious?
-Why?

19:20.812 --> 19:23.710
That music is for a funeral.

19:25.719 --> 19:27.617
Do you know that piece, Vivian?

19:27.626 --> 19:30.525
Yes, it is a piece of Prokofiev. 
Lovely, isn't it?

19:31.533 --> 19:33.432
I better get to the record
store before they sell it out.

19:34.441 --> 19:37.339
Oh, come on, Gwen.
We all have sensitive side.

19:38.348 --> 19:40.246
I do not remember that
you said that last night.

19:57.255 --> 20:00.154
-Thank you.
-Do you want me to wait?

20:00.162 --> 20:02.061
I am sure you have better things 
to do than wait for me.

20:02.070 --> 20:03.968
Oh look, I am sorry about Gwen.

20:03.977 --> 20:06.875
You know why I am here for. 
I don't need to understand your friends?

20:07.884 --> 20:09.783
I'll leave the key here.

20:09.792 --> 20:12.690
I have more important things to
think than how I'll go back.

20:12.699 --> 20:14.597
Thanks anyway!

20:14.606 --> 20:16.504
You're welcome.

20:21.513 --> 20:25.412
From what I see in this agreement,
Dr. Bell walks out with everything.

20:25.421 --> 20:27.219
I've always supported myself.

20:27.328 --> 20:29.226
All I want are my books.

20:31.235 --> 20:33.133
-Is there a third party?
-No.

20:34.142 --> 20:36.041
Rare women, walks out with  
no strings.

20:37.050 --> 20:39.948
What is your ground?

20:41.957 --> 20:43.855
It is not that I have practiced 
this.

20:46.864 --> 20:48.763
It is not easy to talk 
with an attorney.

20:51.771 --> 20:53.670
-Do you like ranch?
-It's different.

20:56.679 --> 20:57.577
There are many crazy people there.

20:57.586 --> 21:01.484
Mr. Warner, I have 35 years.
I want an honest life.

21:01.493 --> 21:03.392
I am leaving a decent marriage 
to see if I can find one.

21:03.400 --> 21:05.299
Not having children helps.

21:05.308 --> 21:08.206
Although our careers served very 
much that purpose all these years.

21:08.215 --> 21:10.113
To bond us togehter.
We were very big on form.

21:12.122 --> 21:17.021
Right friends, a prince
on the wall.

21:20.030 --> 21:23.928
I urge for something we can not 
analyze or rationalize.

21:27.937 --> 21:30.535
I want to break free 
from what I've been.

21:30.844 --> 21:32.742
And your husband?

21:34.751 --> 21:36.650
Martin wants to have me 
no matter how I feel.

21:36.659 --> 21:38.557
-He will not contest?
-No, no.

21:40.566 --> 21:41.464
Well...

21:42.473 --> 21:46.371
-We'll go with mental cruelty.
-We've never treated each other that way.

21:47.380 --> 21:49.279
It's just a formal term.

21:50.288 --> 21:53.186
It is better for law.
A headacke or two.

21:27.195 --> 21:57.093
Sure he refused to
visit in-laws, sometimes.

21:58.102 --> 22:00.001
Maybe I'll be alone 
the rest of my life.

22:01.009 --> 22:04.908
I made a very difficult decision and 
it was not based on a headache or two.

22:10.917 --> 22:12.815
Time for a martini.
Would you like to take one with me?

22:14.824 --> 22:16.722
Please, go on.

22:18.731 --> 22:21.630
Well, the first thing I 
advise my clients 

22:23.638 --> 22:25.537
is not to leave the state 
once the residence is established.

22:26.546 --> 22:29.444
Many leave to San Francisco 
for a break.

22:30.453 --> 22:32.351
Don't misunderstand me,
Mr. Warner.

22:32.360 --> 22:34.259
But that does not happen 
in this case.

22:35.268 --> 22:38.166
No. I trust we can leave the
keys with you any time.

22:42.175 --> 22:43.073
Thank you.

22:47.082 --> 22:49.980
Ok, put your stuff in here.

22:50.989 --> 22:53.888
Lock it up. The changing room
is over there.

22:53.897 --> 22:56.795
-Hello everybody. -This is Joyce.
-Hello, Joyce!

22:57.804 --> 23:00.702
I leave you with the girls.
See you on the floor.

23:00.711 --> 23:01.610
All right.

23:05.618 --> 23:08.517
Cay, I'll like to see you in my office?
Please.

23:11.526 --> 23:13.424
Darrel, where shall I put the key?

23:13.433 --> 23:15.331
-Oh, God!
-I'll tell you where.

23:16.340 --> 23:17.239
Thank you, Silver.

23:18.247 --> 23:20.146
That was not very clever.

23:27.155 --> 23:28.053
Cay.

23:36.662 --> 23:38.960
Do you know how much I love you?

23:44.969 --> 23:47.868
I started to express myself
and ruined everything?

23:49.804 --> 23:51.702
There's nothing to ruin, Darrel

23:53.659 --> 23:55.557
And I've been honest with you
about why.

23:56.566 --> 23:57.464
I know everything.

23:59.473 --> 24:01.371
I can look the other way 
if I had to.

24:11.380 --> 24:13.279
Oh, hi.

24:25.288 --> 24:28.186
-Sorry.
-Frances is awake.

24:28.195 --> 24:30.093
I just thought about ...

24:30.094 --> 24:31.094
having a cup of tea.

24:31.102 --> 24:32.001
Let me get it for you.

24:33.009 --> 24:35.908
Don't bother. I could
use a practice.

24:40.917 --> 24:42.815
Would you, please, go and
sit down?

24:42.824 --> 24:44.722
If she hear us, I wont
get out in less than hour.

24:46.731 --> 24:49.630
I'll come back when it is less 
complicated. 

24:53.638 --> 24:54.537
Shit!

24:56.546 --> 24:58.444
What are you doing?

24:59.453 --> 25:01.351
Shut up!

25:04.360 --> 25:05.259
I'll clean.

25:08.268 --> 25:10.166
Look at my boots.

25:21.175 --> 25:23.073
Please, don't
turn on the light.

25:27.082 --> 25:29.980
What's matter?
You are having a rough night?

25:31.989 --> 25:33.888
You could say that.

25:34.897 --> 25:37.795
Listen, I'm always awake.

25:37.804 --> 25:39.702
Next time you can't sleep,
come to my cottage.

25:41.711 --> 25:43.610
Some company will help.

25:43.618 --> 25:45.517
You'll make me cry.

25:48.526 --> 25:50.424
No.
I'm going to make you some tea.

25:54.433 --> 25:56.331
Is it you, Cay?
- Yeah

25:59.340 --> 26:03.239
Bring me a coke, please?
I have a glass.

26:18.247 --> 26:21.146
-Who is in the kitchen?
-Vivian is making tea.

26:22.155 --> 26:24.053
She is so nice.

26:24.062 --> 26:26.960
This all place has risen 
category since she came.

26:30.969 --> 26:33.868
I spend all night 
struggling with migrene.

26:35.877 --> 26:37.775
You are wearing that one
out, Frances.

26:40.784 --> 26:42.682
No, everything is falling apart.

26:42.691 --> 26:45.589
It is middle of the night.
It will be together by morning.

26:50.598 --> 26:51.497
Ok...

26:53.506 --> 26:55.504
What is falling apart?

26:55.413 --> 26:57.311
The ranch, for example.

26:57.320 --> 27:01.218
Business is bad. I don't think 
it will hold much longer.

27:04.227 --> 27:06.126
Remember the good old days?

27:07.989 --> 27:09.888
Can not drink for the good old days.

27:11.897 --> 27:15.795
If I do sell, I want you 
to come with me.

27:17.804 --> 27:19.702
We do not picture us living
in two rooms togehter.

27:19.711 --> 27:21.610
Oh, It will be bigger than that.

27:23.618 --> 27:25.517
If you come with me 

27:26.526 --> 27:29.424
You can leave the casino 
and go to study art.

27:32.433 --> 27:34.331
Botton yourself up.

27:35.340 --> 27:38.239
Professor does not need
to see your business popping out.

27:38.247 --> 27:41.146
-Where are your pants?
-I have to go.

27:41.155 --> 27:44.053
I will not stay so do not 
squeeze me.

27:46.062 --> 27:49.960
You and Walter are all 
I have left from Glen!

27:49.969 --> 27:51.868
Glen is dead.

27:55.877 --> 27:57.775
No, if I still have you.

27:59.784 --> 28:02.682
Someday I will meet someone
who counts.

28:04.691 --> 28:08.589
Counts?
But look at who your friends are.

28:08.598 --> 28:11.497
Do not ask your support. But
if you stand in my way ...

28:22.506 --> 28:24.404
Now, go to sleep.

28:31.413 --> 28:33.311
I empty out my ice box.

28:35.320 --> 28:37.218
Good night, Frances.

29:12.227 --> 29:13.126
Good morning!

29:16.135 --> 29:17.033
Good morning.

29:17.042 --> 29:19.940
When was the last time you
ride a horse?

29:20.949 --> 29:22.848
I don't even remember.

29:22.856 --> 29:24.755
Then, take off your reading
glasses and come over here.

29:45.764 --> 29:47.662
I did not know you were 
painting, Frances?

29:48.671 --> 29:50.569
The last supper.

29:53.578 --> 29:56.477
Oh, looks like someone did not pack
riding cloths.

29:56.485 --> 29:58.384
I thought my riding days are
behind me.

29:58.393 --> 30:00.291
Here. Try this to see the size. 
- Oh.

30:03.300 --> 30:06.198
Reserve me place in the mental
for me.

30:07.207 --> 30:09.106
Good times are hard in the end. 

30:14.115 --> 30:16.013
Sorry about your friend 
the other day.

30:16.022 --> 30:18.920
I temporary lost my sense 
of humor.

30:19.929 --> 30:21.827
It is awful to forget
how to laugh.

30:22.836 --> 30:26.735
I'm always get-by by laughing. 
That what you are going through
takes real courage.

